    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="803"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.48/1365: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-01T19:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1921—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 3—1.10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Department’s 3, January 13, 8 p.m.<note n="34" xml:id="d803fn34">Not
                        printed.</note> After evacuation of Crimea French Government took over
                    available assets of Wrangel government to help cover expenses of caring for
                    refugees. These assets include war and merchant vessels of which French
                    Government with Wrangel’s consent has now sold four minor vessels. Majority of
                    Wrangel fleet is under French control in port of Bizerte.</p>
                <p>According to statement of local Russian mission supplies belonging to Wrangel
                    government valued at more than 100,000,000 francs have been taken over by the
                    French. Friction has resulted from French action in seizing and disposing of
                    some of this property without granting Russians facilities for checking total
                    value.</p>
                <p>Particulars by mail. Repeated to Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
